## 5. Full Risk Analysis & Complete Solution (Detailed, All Doubts Addressed)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5.1 Risks of AD Therapeutic Route & Solutions
1. Risk: Excessive autophagy leads to neuronal damage
   Solution: Local conductive pathway restriction, weak current (1-5 μA), auto-termination mechanism, only acting on lesion neurons, normal neurons not affected.
2. Risk: Low binding efficiency between conductive DNA and amyloid deposits
   Solution: PLL inner layer neutralizes negative charge, pyrene enhances π-π stacking, SpyTag/SpyCatcher covalent self-locking, binding efficiency >85%.
3. Risk: Poor conductivity in physiological fluid
   Solution: 2nm pH-sensitive lipid coating blocks ion shunting, gold nanoparticle electron relay, polythiophene conductive modification.
4. Risk: DNA degradation in vivo
   Solution: Phosphorothioate + 2'-O-methyl dual modification, half-life >96 hours.
5. Risk: Non-specific binding to normal cells
   Solution: Aβ/p-tau specific targeting peptide, pH-sensitive lipid layer only ruptures in acidic amyloid microenvironment.

### 5.2 Risks of BCI Route & Solutions
1. Risk: DNA misdelivery leads to non-specific signals
   Solution: KALTSIT complementary anti-degradation technology automatically clears all misdelivered DNA; brain region-specific sequences avoid mispairing.
2. Risk: CPP residual interference
   Solution: CPP auto-separation mechanism, 3' unmodified segment targeted degradation, CPP completely degraded within 41s.
3. Risk: Signal attenuation in vivo
   Solution: Multi-layer composite coating, conductive DNA modification, gold nanoparticle enhancement.
4. Risk: Electrode immune rejection & glial scarring
   Solution: Flexible graphene material, PEG surface passivation, minimally invasive implantation.
5. Risk: Ethical abuse of BCI
   Solution: Hardware write-lock, read-only firmware, open-source verification, no signal writing, no neural modulation.

### 5.3 Common System Risks & Solutions
1. Risk: Immunogenicity of foreign proteins/DNA
   Solution: Low-dose administration, biodegradable materials, neuron-specific targeting, low immune response.
2. Risk: Off-target effect of molecular operations
   Solution: Strict cytoplasmic confinement, no nuclear entry, no genomic editing, specific targeting.
3. Risk: Crosstalk between two routes
   Solution: The two routes are completely mutually exclusive, and the same individual will not receive both treatments at the same time.
