## 6. Full Feasibility Analysis (Literature-Supported, Evidence-Based)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Material Feasibility: All components can be commercially synthesized or biologically expressed, no de novo molecular design required.
2. Biological Feasibility: All mechanisms are supported by top peer-reviewed literature and verified in cell/animal models.
3. Engineering Feasibility: Coating, delivery, electrode, and electrical stimulation systems are standard neuroengineering technologies.
4. Safety Feasibility: All parameters are within clinical safe range, cytoplasmic-only operation, no genomic editing, read-only BCI.
5. Translational Feasibility: The two routes are developed independently, with mature technologies and clear clinical transformation path.
